               <msContents>
                  <summary>Author <persName xml:lang="tu" key="person_90747748"
                        ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/90747748/">Şem‘ī Şemullah (d. ca. 1602)</persName>
                     composed this Ottoman Turkish prose interpretive commentary on the Persian
                        <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Būstān</title> (Fragrant Orchard), of
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard" key="person_120724759"
                        ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/120724759/">Saʻdī</persName>. Completed by
                        <persName role="scr" xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc">Ibrahīm bin Velī</persName> on
                        <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1586-01-17">Friday, end of Muḥarram 994
                        AH (17 Jan 1586 CE)</date>, it would appear to be one of the earliest-known
                     extant copies to survive. British linguist <persName role="pat ins fmo"
                        key="person_102326800" ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/102326800/">Sir William
                        Jones (1746–1794)</persName> possibly acquired the volume while a
                     student.</summary>

